Extensive practitioner experience in the Cumberland Plain is that sites with poor groundcovers do not naturally recover groundcovers without extensive restoration (e.g. scalping) although minor gains can be made through competitive exclusion
Grassy-groundcover' (scalp and seed) monitoring by GS LLS shows very good initial results but low resilience and a natural attrition of gains over time
